chip.type: deterministic PRN (+1/-1) from (code, run_id, role) repeated per chip

message.type: deterministic low-rate PRN (+1/-1), reference equals injected message

mux.metric: rho_X = corr( boxcar((envX_hp * chipX)), boxcar(msg) ); delta = rho_B - rho_C
mux.note: Claim-ready discrimination requires MOD_OFF to collapse near 0 under this reference-correct metric.

definitions.goal: Selective listening in a shared broadcast medium: matched receiver B decodes injected message; mismatch receiver C does not.
non_claims: This is engineered comms (spread-spectrum + matched filtering), not quantum effects or biological translation.
